        "title": "Hashmap side by side comparison",
        "body": "<p>I am trying to find out if there are more occurrences of a \"greater\" (ASCII value) character than a \"lesser\" character. I've counted all of the occurrences of each character into a hashmap. I am wondering how I can compare two key values side by side? I basically want this to be like an array where I can compare if hashmap.value[i + 1] > hashmap.value[i].<\/p>\n\n<p>String (\"ssppprr\") --> true\nString (\"sspprrr\") --> false<\/p>\n\n<p>Here is my code:<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>    for (int i = 0; i &lt; str.length(); i++) {\n        if (!map.containsKey(str.charAt(i))) {\n            map.put(str.charAt(i), 1);\n        } else{\n            int x = map.get(str.charAt(i));\n            map.put(str.charAt(i), ++x);\n        }\n    }\n\n    for (Entry&lt;Character, Integer&gt; e : map.entrySet()) {\n        Character firstLetter = e.getKey();\n        Integer firstAvailable = map.get(firstLetter);\n        //compare and return false if true\n    }\n    return true;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
